1
00:02:45,004 --> 00:02:47,677
I remember when Roy brought Irma home.

2
00:02:48,244 --> 00:02:52,635
He took me aside and said,
"Mama, I think this is the one."

3
00:02:53,004 --> 00:02:55,518
I wanted him to stay and run the farm.

4
00:02:55,604 --> 00:02:58,038
But he said no, he'd rather be dead.

5
00:02:58,124 --> 00:03:00,797
- Dad, time for the toast.
- I'm telling a story.

6
00:03:01,924 --> 00:03:05,394
I got so mad,
I hauled off and popped him one.

7
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,919
Gave him a shiner on his wedding day.

8
00:03:08,724 --> 00:03:11,522
Let's get Roy and Irma up here!
Where are they?

9
00:03:12,084 --> 00:03:15,156
Come on, let's go,
before they enter their 26th!

10
00:03:18,924 --> 00:03:21,597
- Are we all here?
- Yeah, we are!

11
00:03:25,524 --> 00:03:29,403
I remember when Roy and Irma
first joined our congregation.

12
00:03:29,724 --> 00:03:32,079
What was it, 21 years ago?

13
00:03:33,284 --> 00:03:36,401
They had more energy
and more goodwill toward each other...

14
00:03:36,484 --> 00:03:38,042
than any couple I ever knew.

15
00:03:38,124 --> 00:03:41,321
The goodwill is still there.
I don't know about the energy.

16
00:03:42,324 --> 00:03:45,122
I remember their first
pancake breakfast.

17
00:03:45,204 --> 00:03:48,799
Roy at the griddle,
Irma right behind him with the batter.

18
00:03:48,924 --> 00:03:52,678
As soon as he'd scoop up one pancake,
she'd plop down another one.

19
00:03:52,764 --> 00:03:55,073
Never a cross word between them.

20
00:03:56,004 --> 00:03:58,996
In fact, the more pressure
that was on them...

21
00:03:59,084 --> 00:04:01,882
the more they seemed
to enjoy each other.

22
00:04:02,364 --> 00:04:05,879
I don't know of any other couple
in our congregation...

23
00:04:06,244 --> 00:04:08,633
or in this town, for that matter...

24
00:04:08,884 --> 00:04:11,034
more devoted to each other...

25
00:04:11,884 --> 00:04:14,796
more in love than Roy and Irma.

26
00:04:16,204 --> 00:04:18,638
I'm grateful to have them with us...

27
00:04:18,884 --> 00:04:22,160
because we're all beneficiaries
of that partnership.

28
00:04:22,564 --> 00:04:24,236
Happy anniversary.

29
00:04:34,924 --> 00:04:36,403
Get an ambulance.

30
00:04:37,524 --> 00:04:38,877
Is he drunk?

31
00:04:47,524 --> 00:04:48,843
Dear God...

32
00:04:49,124 --> 00:04:53,117
help this couple find the wisdom
to work out their differences...

33
00:04:53,204 --> 00:04:55,877
and rekindle the joy of their marriage.

34
00:04:56,164 --> 00:05:00,635
Shed your light upon them, so that they
may continue to grow and flourish...

35
00:05:00,724 --> 00:05:04,194
in the love that they have for you
and for each other.

36
00:05:04,484 --> 00:05:05,758
Amen.

37
00:05:09,244 --> 00:05:11,264
Roy, I heard what
happened the other night.

38
00:05:11,265 --> 00:05:13,283
Are you all right?

39
00:05:13,364 --> 00:05:16,322
- I'm fine. It was nothing.
- Scared me half to death.

40
00:05:16,684 --> 00:05:20,472
We took him to the hospital,
but everything turned out okay.

41
00:05:20,564 --> 00:05:22,122
Thank goodness.

42
00:05:24,724 --> 00:05:27,557
I think it has something to do
with the headaches.

43
00:05:28,124 --> 00:05:31,719
I mean, he's been getting terrible,
terrible headaches.

44
00:05:31,804 --> 00:05:35,001
- Have you seen a doctor about this?
- Every one in the phone book.

45
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:37,552
- He's had a CAT scan.
- Insurance will cut me loose.

46
00:05:37,644 --> 00:05:39,760
- Did they find anything?
- No.

47
00:05:42,044 --> 00:05:46,162
I think it's...
His doctor seems to think it's stress.

48
00:05:46,484 --> 00:05:48,395
Has your work been stressful?

49
00:05:49,164 --> 00:05:51,120
There's some pressure on me.

50
00:05:51,324 --> 00:05:53,281
Honey, there's a lot
of pressure on you.

51
00:05:53,282 --> 00:05:55,237
No more than usual.

52
00:05:56,644 --> 00:06:00,193
He used to have to handle
just the tractors.

53
00:06:00,284 --> 00:06:03,117
But now, he has to take
care of everything...

54
00:06:03,204 --> 00:06:07,436
from the cultivators to the combines...

55
00:06:08,244 --> 00:06:09,233
Yikes!

56
00:06:09,324 --> 00:06:12,999
So you could say that maybe
these headaches are work-related.

57
00:06:13,524 --> 00:06:15,037
They could be.

58
00:06:16,444 --> 00:06:19,436
Is there anything else in your life
that's been bothering you?

59
00:06:19,524 --> 00:06:23,199
You can always find something.

60
00:06:25,604 --> 00:06:28,118
Honey, I think there's been some...

61
00:06:29,324 --> 00:06:31,679
strain between us lately.

62
00:06:31,764 --> 00:06:34,039
Sure, there's been some strain.

63
00:06:35,004 --> 00:06:38,394
Are you having any problems with...

64
00:06:39,564 --> 00:06:40,792
intimacy?

65
00:06:41,404 --> 00:06:42,439
Not really.

66
00:06:42,524 --> 00:06:44,992
We haven't had much intimacy lately.

67
00:06:45,084 --> 00:06:47,040
Because of the headaches?

68
00:06:50,844 --> 00:06:51,833
Yes.

69
00:06:56,004 --> 00:06:58,564
Would you like to talk to me alone?

70
00:07:03,324 --> 00:07:05,758
Whatever it is, just get it out, honey.

71
00:07:05,844 --> 00:07:08,358
I don't even have to know what it is.

72
00:07:08,444 --> 00:07:11,277
I mean, just talk it out with him, okay?

73
00:07:11,724 --> 00:07:12,713
Please?

74
00:07:12,844 --> 00:07:15,404
Irma, if you want,
you can wait in the chapel.

75
00:07:15,484 --> 00:07:18,396
No, I'd like Irma to stay.

76
00:07:18,964 --> 00:07:20,397
Better still.

77
00:07:24,244 --> 00:07:26,633
Tell us what's on your mind, Roy.

78
00:07:37,804 --> 00:07:39,203
I've been...

79
00:07:39,804 --> 00:07:42,637
struggling with something
for a long time.

80
00:07:46,964 --> 00:07:49,683
I prayed for years for it to go away.

81
00:07:51,484 --> 00:07:52,963
But it won't.

82
00:07:56,204 --> 00:07:57,273
Go on.

83
00:08:01,644 --> 00:08:03,874
I was born in the wrong body.

84
00:08:06,404 --> 00:08:09,237
I'm a woman. I've known it all my life.

85
00:08:10,684 --> 00:08:12,163
Oh, my gosh, Roy.

86
00:08:12,244 --> 00:08:15,361
Good grief, Roy...

87
00:08:16,804 --> 00:08:18,635
I don't know what to say.

88
00:08:18,724 --> 00:08:20,396
I don't either, except...

89
00:08:20,484 --> 00:08:23,601
I love Irma very much.

90
00:08:23,684 --> 00:08:27,518
The last thing I want to do
is cause her any pain.

91
00:08:31,804 --> 00:08:34,637
- Roy, are you having an affair?
- No, Irma.

92
00:08:36,964 --> 00:08:40,354
But this doesn't make any sense.

93
00:08:40,884 --> 00:08:42,875
Roy, I have to agree.

94
00:08:43,564 --> 00:08:47,113
I mean, you've been married to Irma
for 25 years.

95
00:08:47,444 --> 00:08:50,800
You have two wonderful children,
and suddenly, out of nowhere...

96
00:08:50,884 --> 00:08:53,000
you make this strange declaration?

97
00:08:53,084 --> 00:08:55,962
It's not out of nowhere.
I've been hiding it for years.

98
00:08:56,044 --> 00:08:59,559
It's been an agony.
I can't go on living my life like this.

99
00:08:59,644 --> 00:09:01,077
I'd rather die.

100
00:09:01,164 --> 00:09:03,803
Oh, my God, do you mean that?

101
00:09:03,884 --> 00:09:04,839
Yes.

102
00:09:08,644 --> 00:09:12,956
Before you jump to any more conclusions
about yourself...

103
00:09:14,284 --> 00:09:17,401
what exactly appeals to you
about being a woman?

104
00:09:18,804 --> 00:09:21,443
What appeals to you about being a man?

105
00:09:21,564 --> 00:09:22,963
Many things.

106
00:09:23,244 --> 00:09:27,032
Beginning with the fact
that this is the form God chose for me.

107
00:09:27,124 --> 00:09:30,673
But I believe that God meant for me
to be something else.

108
00:09:31,684 --> 00:09:34,244
- Meaning?
- Meaning I'd like to...

109
00:09:35,524 --> 00:09:37,355
have the operation...

110
00:09:38,204 --> 00:09:39,842
to change my sex.

111
00:09:44,324 --> 00:09:45,962
Oh, my God, Roy.

112
00:09:52,604 --> 00:09:57,359
Obviously, this is a lot
for us to comprehend, Roy.

113
00:09:57,444 --> 00:09:59,639
You know, I'd like to go home.

114
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:02,557
I think this would be
a good point to stop.

115
00:10:02,644 --> 00:10:05,112
Obviously, I wasn't prepared for this.

116
00:10:05,204 --> 00:10:09,482
If you two could give me a few days
to do some research, think this over...

117
00:10:09,564 --> 00:10:12,032
Roy, I'm not exactly sure...

118
00:10:12,124 --> 00:10:16,356
how I'm going to counsel you at this
point, but I promise I'm not giving up.

119
00:10:16,844 --> 00:10:19,199
I just want to be sure that...

120
00:10:19,884 --> 00:10:23,320
you'll still accept me
as a member of the congregation.

121
00:10:23,844 --> 00:10:26,119
Heck, you're the only
fellow I can get...

122
00:10:26,204 --> 00:10:28,280
to nail together the
nativity every year.

123
00:10:28,281 --> 00:10:30,356
You think I'll let you go that easy?

124
00:11:08,404 --> 00:11:09,393
What?

125
00:11:10,564 --> 00:11:12,043
What did I do?

126
00:11:12,604 --> 00:11:14,083
Nothing, honey.

127
00:11:15,404 --> 00:11:17,042
Then someone talk.

128
00:11:18,724 --> 00:11:20,077
How was school?

129
00:11:20,964 --> 00:11:23,194
Don't talk to me, talk to each other.

130
00:11:26,844 --> 00:11:29,119
Your dad and I both had a long day...

131
00:11:29,204 --> 00:11:32,241
and we just don't feel like talking.

132
00:11:34,564 --> 00:11:35,997
Talk anyway.

133
00:11:39,164 --> 00:11:40,756
Finish your peas.

134
00:11:49,924 --> 00:11:52,757
Irma, we couldn't go on
the way things were.

135
00:11:52,844 --> 00:11:54,641
Look at how unhappy I've made you.

136
00:11:54,724 --> 00:11:56,282
I'm not unhappy.

137
00:11:56,444 --> 00:11:58,719
There's been a strain
between us for years.

138
00:11:58,804 --> 00:12:02,357
- This is supposed to make it better?
- I'm hoping so. Yes.

139
00:12:05,964 --> 00:12:08,319
Did you feel this way when you met me?

140
00:12:08,404 --> 00:12:10,122
I suspected it, yes.

141
00:12:10,364 --> 00:12:13,754
Then what in heaven's name
were you thinking of on our wedding day?

142
00:12:13,844 --> 00:12:16,756
- That you were the one for me.
- Meaning what?

143
00:12:16,844 --> 00:12:19,802
Meaning that I loved you, I love you.

144
00:12:22,804 --> 00:12:24,556
When we're in bed...

145
00:12:25,724 --> 00:12:28,113
are you a man or are you a woman?

146
00:12:28,844 --> 00:12:32,962
- I make love to you as myself.
- But are you a man, or are you a woman?

147
00:12:34,164 --> 00:12:38,555
Sometimes, I imagine
I have a different body. Not always.

148
00:12:41,084 --> 00:12:44,997
Sometimes, the female part takes over.

149
00:12:47,164 --> 00:12:50,042
I have some books you could read.

150
00:12:52,604 --> 00:12:53,753
Books?

151
00:12:53,964 --> 00:12:56,034
About my condition.

152
00:12:57,244 --> 00:12:59,041
About the operation.

153
00:12:59,244 --> 00:13:03,635
You mean, you expect us to go on
living together after you do this thing?

154
00:13:04,844 --> 00:13:06,402
If you'll have me.

155
00:13:06,684 --> 00:13:09,676
Frankly, honey,
there's no way you're a woman.

156
00:13:10,204 --> 00:13:12,638
Only a man could be this selfish.

157
00:13:13,764 --> 00:13:16,073
- Mom?
- What is it, Patty?

158
00:13:16,524 --> 00:13:20,119
- Could you come out here for a minute?
- Is it something important?

159
00:13:20,764 --> 00:13:21,799
Yes.

160
00:13:29,444 --> 00:13:30,843
What is it?

161
00:13:31,444 --> 00:13:33,082
Mom, it happened.

162
00:13:36,844 --> 00:13:38,357
Just a minute.

163
00:13:40,124 --> 00:13:42,922
- You all right, Patty?
- It's nothing.

164
00:13:47,804 --> 00:13:50,398
- You want me to show you how to...
- No!

165
00:13:56,444 --> 00:13:58,116
Is she all right?

166
00:13:59,604 --> 00:14:01,242
She got her period.

167
00:14:01,324 --> 00:14:04,236
Poor kid. She sounded so scared.

168
00:14:06,124 --> 00:14:10,117
You are not to breathe a word to her
about any of this. Do you understand?

169
00:14:10,204 --> 00:14:12,081
She has to know about
me at some point.

170
00:14:12,082 --> 00:14:13,958
No, I won't allow you to do this.

171
00:14:14,044 --> 00:14:16,478
- There's a way to handle it properly.
- No!

172
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:19,795
- Absolutely not!
- Irma, it's not going to go away.

173
00:14:19,884 --> 00:14:22,557
Get out! Get out of my bedroom!

174
00:14:26,564 --> 00:14:30,352
- I'll sleep on the couch.
- No, I don't want you in this house.

175
00:14:31,564 --> 00:14:32,917
All right.

176
00:16:17,444 --> 00:16:21,676
If this is only a separation, why are
you throwing out all of Dad's stuff?

177
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:26,994
Is that what you're wearing to school?
Go change your clothes.

178
00:16:27,924 --> 00:16:29,039
Why?

179
00:16:29,924 --> 00:16:31,880
Don't argue, just do it.

180
00:17:11,764 --> 00:17:13,243
How you doing, Roy?

181
00:17:19,164 --> 00:17:21,803
- Morning, Roy.
- Morning, Bob.

182
00:17:22,804 --> 00:17:24,999
Another goddamn day.

183
00:17:27,564 --> 00:17:30,124
Not a damn thing we can
do about it, either.

184
00:17:31,484 --> 00:17:32,963
See you later.

185
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:46,164
So, I talked to a pastor in Akron.

186
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:49,163
He was counselling a married couple...

187
00:17:49,244 --> 00:17:51,917
and the husband said that
he was a homosexual.

188
00:17:52,644 --> 00:17:56,762
He was able to persuade the husband
not to act on his inclinations...

189
00:17:56,844 --> 00:17:58,721
and he saved the marriage.

190
00:17:59,204 --> 00:18:02,640
- Sounds hopeful.
- I'm feeling very hopeful about this.

191
00:18:02,724 --> 00:18:04,237
Now, what this pastor did...

192
00:18:04,324 --> 00:18:07,475
he referred this couple
to a chapter in the Bible...

193
00:18:07,564 --> 00:18:11,000
which I think
very elegantly supports our case.

194
00:18:14,204 --> 00:18:16,160
Did you bring your Bible?

195
00:18:16,684 --> 00:18:18,163
No, I'm sorry.

196
00:18:18,484 --> 00:18:20,759
No problem. You can look on with me.

197
00:18:21,804 --> 00:18:25,353
Ephesians, Chapter 5, Verse 28.

198
00:18:27,764 --> 00:18:31,518
"So ought men to love their wives
as their own bodies.

199
00:18:31,884 --> 00:18:34,603
"He that loveth his
wife loveth himself.

200
00:18:34,724 --> 00:18:37,636
"For no man ever yet
hated his own flesh."

201
00:18:39,044 --> 00:18:42,639
"For no man ever yet
hated his own flesh."

202
00:18:43,844 --> 00:18:44,833
Bingo!

203
00:18:46,564 --> 00:18:48,879
In other words, men
couple with women to

204
00:18:48,880 --> 00:18:51,194
bring out the female
side of their nature.

205
00:18:51,564 --> 00:18:53,600
And the mistake that Roy's making...

206
00:18:53,684 --> 00:18:57,802
is he's looking to himself for
that balance, instead of to you.

207
00:18:58,924 --> 00:18:59,913
I see.

208
00:19:00,004 --> 00:19:04,202
We need to just make Roy realize
that you're all the woman he needs.

209
00:19:04,284 --> 00:19:07,162
He doesn't have to make himself
into a woman...

210
00:19:07,244 --> 00:19:09,200
parade around in dresses and such.

211
00:19:09,284 --> 00:19:13,562
Heck, that's just plain egotistical of
him, to think that he can do it all.

212
00:19:13,644 --> 00:19:16,238
Men need women for completion.

213
00:19:17,284 --> 00:19:20,242
Why do you think we call our wives
our better halves?

214
00:19:21,524 --> 00:19:25,358
Roy has always felt
overly responsible for things.

215
00:19:25,724 --> 00:19:27,476
He used to come home from work...

216
00:19:27,564 --> 00:19:32,080
do a couple of hours of chores, and then
stay up till midnight paying bills.

217
00:19:32,164 --> 00:19:35,042
No wonder he gets these
terrible headaches.

218
00:19:35,804 --> 00:19:39,001
That's why I decided
to take over doing the taxes.

219
00:19:41,644 --> 00:19:44,363
Irma, let me ask you something.

220
00:19:45,204 --> 00:19:47,957
And this may just be a stab in the dark.

221
00:19:50,524 --> 00:19:54,437
Do you think you might have unknowingly
added to his confusion?

222
00:19:57,724 --> 00:19:59,794
I don't know what you mean.

223
00:20:00,324 --> 00:20:04,442
Please understand, I'm not questioning
your love for Roy in any way.

224
00:20:04,524 --> 00:20:08,358
It's just that you're
a very strong-willed person...

225
00:20:08,564 --> 00:20:12,557
and I'm just wondering if you often take
the upper hand with Roy.

226
00:20:12,804 --> 00:20:14,283
Do you mean...

227
00:20:15,204 --> 00:20:17,593
have I emasculated him?

228
00:20:18,564 --> 00:20:22,557
I haven't made myself clear. Forgive me.

229
00:20:24,404 --> 00:20:25,439
Gosh!

230
00:20:25,524 --> 00:20:30,314
I think it's a problem that
every modern couple is having right now.

231
00:20:31,044 --> 00:20:33,114
Who's the head of the household?

232
00:20:33,204 --> 00:20:36,480
Is it the one who brings home
the biggest pay check?

233
00:20:36,604 --> 00:20:38,823
Heck, I'm not going to
win on that one. Not

234
00:20:38,824 --> 00:20:41,041
with what I make on a pastor's salary.

235
00:20:41,564 --> 00:20:43,236
But I don't work.

236
00:20:43,604 --> 00:20:45,003
I know that.

237
00:20:45,404 --> 00:20:48,840
From what I've observed,
you've been a very good wife.

238
00:20:51,644 --> 00:20:53,874
I don't know what I'm doing wrong.

239
00:20:53,964 --> 00:20:57,673
I don't know either, Irma,
but we'll figure it out.

240
00:21:32,204 --> 00:21:36,163
I keep smelling this goddamn perfume.
Where the hell is it coming from?

241
00:21:36,244 --> 00:21:38,314
I think it's Roy over there.

242
00:21:38,724 --> 00:21:42,034
Roy, you dog, have you been stepping out
on your wife?

243
00:21:42,124 --> 00:21:44,433
- No.
- Hey, I'm not saying a word.

244
00:21:44,524 --> 00:21:47,163
I love Irma dearly, I'd
never do that to her.

245
00:21:47,244 --> 00:21:48,757
If you say so.

246
00:21:48,964 --> 00:21:52,036
- I do say so.
- Buddy, there's no judgment here.

247
00:21:52,364 --> 00:21:54,832
Whoever the new lady is, I say enjoy it.

248
00:21:55,284 --> 00:21:57,718
- I wish I could trade my wife in.
- You want mine?

249
00:21:57,804 --> 00:21:59,954
She still has a few good miles left.

